Coal India, Reliance, Redington: India Equity Preview

-- B y   A n d r e w   M a c A s k i l l
-- 
2011-07-05T02:32:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-05/coal-india-reliance-industries-redington-india-equity-preview.html
(Corrects time reference in third paragraph to yesterday.)  The following companies may have
unusual price changes in India trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the last close, unless
otherwise stated.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, rose
0.3 percent to 18,814.48. The BSE 200 Index rose 0.6 percent to
2,328.98. The S&P CNX Nifty Index on the National Stock Exchange
rose 0.4 percent to 5,650.50.  Ashok Leyland Ltd. (AL)  : The truckmaker sold 8,009
vehicles in June, a decline of 4.6 percent from the same month a
year ago, according to an e-mailed statement yesterday. The
company exported 1,185 units in the month. The shares rose 2.8
percent to 49.8 rupees.  Coal India Ltd. (COAL)  : Workers at the worldâ€™s largest
producer of the fuel threatened to go on a strike from Aug. 8 to
Aug. 10 protesting a delay in wage increases, Rajendra Prasad
Singh, general secretary at Indian National Trade Union Congress,
said. The stock gained 2.8 percent to 395.1 rupees.  Reliance Industries Ltd. (RIL)  : Reliance Trends, a
Reliance Industries unit, expects to double the number of its
retail stores to 100 by the end of this year, Chief Executive
Officer Arun Sirdeshmukh said in Hyderabad yesterday. The shares
rose 0.8 percent to 868.4 rupees.  Redington India Ltd. (REDI)  : Synnex Technology
International Corp. (2347 TT) sold 15.9 million shares of the
Indian supply chain services company for 1.46 billion rupees, or
91.9 rupees per share, Taipei-based Synnex said in an exchange
filing. The stock was unchanged at 88.95 rupees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
